WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:15.348 --> 00:00:18.476
- [Frank Jr.] Come on. Dad. Do it.
- [Frank] All right. all right. all right.

3
00:00:19.269 --> 00:00:21.729
Once upon a time.
in the middle of the night.

4
00:00:21.813 --> 00:00:24.399
two dead men. they got up to fight.

5
00:00:24.482 --> 00:00:26.193
Back-to-back. they faced each other.

6
00:00:26.276 --> 00:00:29.071
they drew their swords
and they shot each other.

7
00:00:29.154 --> 00:00:31.823
- [chuckles]
- Stupid.

8
00:00:31.906 --> 00:00:34.367
What do you mean. "stupid"?
It's not stupid. it's nonsense.

9
00:00:34.451 --> 00:00:37.620
- Nonsense is different from stupid.
- Yeah. then it's stupid nonsense.

10
00:00:37.704 --> 00:00:38.747
Stop that.

11
00:00:40.123 --> 00:00:43.000
Hey. Lis. do the second verse.
Show him how it's done.

12
00:00:43.084 --> 00:00:47.380
One was blind and the other couldn't see.
so they chose a dumb man for a referee.

13
00:00:48.048 --> 00:00:50.859
The blind man went to see fair play.
and the dumb man went to shout. "Hooray!"

14
00:00:50.883 --> 00:00:51.884
- Oh!
- [chuckles]

15
00:00:51.968 --> 00:00:53.219
Attagirl.

16
00:00:53.678 --> 00:00:57.974
See. before smartphones and all that
Internet crap. this is how people got by.

17
00:00:58.058 --> 00:01:00.435
- So boring.
- It's not boring.

18
00:01:01.394 --> 00:01:02.395
Hey...

19
00:01:02.479 --> 00:01:04.814
[Lisa gasps] Look! There it is!

20
00:01:12.739 --> 00:01:15.908
I read at school that she represents
everything good about America.

21
00:01:15.992 --> 00:01:17.327
[Frank] That's about right.

22
00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:19.558
Is that why you have to go and fight?

23
00:01:19.621 --> 00:01:22.165
Dad goes away
so he can kill lots of hajjis.

24
00:01:22.249 --> 00:01:24.049
- How many have you wasted anyway. Dad?
- Hey!

25
00:01:24.083 --> 00:01:26.169
Don't you ever say that again.
You got that?

26
00:01:26.252 --> 00:01:27.420
Do you got it?

27
00:02:09.086 --> 00:02:11.088
Yeah. that's good. I appreciate it.

28
00:02:25.186 --> 00:02:26.626
[Frank] Ma'am. excuse me. but. um...

29
00:02:27.189 --> 00:02:28.669
just get a little bit of that coffee?

30
00:02:34.111 --> 00:02:36.198
Thank you. No. no. Just. uh...

31
00:02:36.281 --> 00:02:39.242
three eggs. over easy.
some bacon. sourdough toast. yeah?

32
00:02:39.325 --> 00:02:40.925
[woman]
You moving into the neighborhood?

33
00:02:42.412 --> 00:02:45.122
- Depends on the eggs.
- We don't get many hipsters around here.

34
00:02:45.207 --> 00:02:47.375
- Yeah. well. you still don't. lady.
- Mm-hmm.

35
00:02:48.626 --> 00:02:53.172
I need. uh. three eggs over easy.
side of bacon and some sourdough toast.

36
00:03:06.478 --> 00:03:07.937
[phone ringing]

37
00:03:11.065 --> 00:03:12.066
Yeah?

38
00:03:13.651 --> 00:03:16.112
Hipster! It's for you.

39
00:03:17.614 --> 00:03:19.258
- That can't be.
- [woman] I'm telling you.

40
00:03:19.282 --> 00:03:22.285
This guy just described you
like he was standing beside me.

41
00:03:39.135 --> 00:03:41.554
- Don't be all day on there.
- Yeah.

42
00:03:46.393 --> 00:03:49.604
- You got the wrong guy.
- [man] Yeah. I don't think so.

43
00:03:50.187 --> 00:03:52.607
Unless I'm not talking to Frank Castle?

44
00:03:53.816 --> 00:03:56.486
You know. let's not waste time.
You're Frank Castle. right?

45
00:03:57.070 --> 00:03:58.738
Frank Castle. the dead man?

46
00:04:02.575 --> 00:04:05.828
- Makes two of us now.
- You're more right than you know.

47
00:04:06.829 --> 00:04:08.998
You're not the only ghost
in this town. Frank.

48
00:04:09.081 --> 00:04:12.669
Hey. did you ever get that disk
that I left for you at your house?

49
00:04:14.211 --> 00:04:16.631
Yeah. Yeah. I got it.

50
00:04:16.714 --> 00:04:18.132
Did you watch it?

51
00:04:18.215 --> 00:04:22.219
"Micro." What is that?
Is that... Is that some sort of name?

52
00:04:22.303 --> 00:04:23.763
Sure. That'll do for now.

53
00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:27.100
You got something you want
to discuss with me. why don't you...

54
00:04:27.475 --> 00:04:29.352
Why don't you come on down here. huh?

55
00:04:30.312 --> 00:04:33.022
Buy you a cup of coffee. talk about it.

56
00:04:33.105 --> 00:04:35.232
You know.
I don't think that would end so well.

57
00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:37.234
You need to understand first.

58
00:04:37.319 --> 00:04:39.904
You need to really know
why you can't kill me.

59
00:04:41.531 --> 00:04:44.033
- Then we can meet.
- [line disconnects]

60
00:04:50.540 --> 00:04:51.624
Delicious.

61
00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:11.060
[Frank panting]

62
00:05:11.143 --> 00:05:12.186
[dog barking]

63
00:05:14.522 --> 00:05:15.940
[panting]

64
00:05:18.067 --> 00:05:19.235
[man] Hey!

65
00:05:42.592 --> 00:05:44.301
[breathing heavily]

66
00:06:46.155 --> 00:06:47.240
Shit.

67
00:06:49.241 --> 00:06:51.243
[theme music playing]

68
00:08:03.149 --> 00:08:04.526
[Maria] Mmm.

69
00:08:09.947 --> 00:08:11.032
Hey.

70
00:08:12.324 --> 00:08:13.660
What time is it?

71
00:08:13.743 --> 00:08:14.744
No!

72
00:08:14.827 --> 00:08:16.412
[breathes heavily]

73
00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:25.171
[grunts]

74
00:08:31.553 --> 00:08:33.054
[breathing heavily]

75
00:08:44.816 --> 00:08:46.568
[Ahmad panting]

76
00:08:46.651 --> 00:08:48.110
[interrogator speaking Pashto]

77
00:08:49.779 --> 00:08:50.780
[Ahmad grunts]

78
00:09:03.585 --> 00:09:06.465
- [soldier in English] What's he saying?
- [interrogator] Nothing useful.

79
00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:08.631
[soldier] We sure he's got anything?

80
00:09:08.715 --> 00:09:10.859
[interrogator]
You questioning my intelligence. soldier?

81
00:09:10.883 --> 00:09:13.177
Please. I'm not a terrorist.

82
00:09:13.260 --> 00:09:16.097
I have a family. children. I have...
[panting]

83
00:09:19.976 --> 00:09:22.604
[interrogator speaking Pashto]

84
00:09:30.903 --> 00:09:32.023
[soldier in English] Do it.

85
00:09:36.242 --> 00:09:37.910
[grunts]

86
00:09:41.122 --> 00:09:42.123
[glass shatters]

87
00:10:04.103 --> 00:10:05.354
Morning. Frank.

88
00:10:07.356 --> 00:10:08.650
So what brings you here?

89
00:10:10.401 --> 00:10:13.821
Curt... there's somebody
who's coming after me.

90
00:10:14.155 --> 00:10:15.447
Somebody knows I'm alive.

91
00:10:16.782 --> 00:10:18.409
He calls himself Micro.

92
00:10:19.619 --> 00:10:22.204
- You wanna know if he got it from me?
- Look. it's a short list.

93
00:10:22.288 --> 00:10:23.873
- I'm not saying...
- Come on. Frank.

94
00:10:23.956 --> 00:10:26.583
- I would never give you up.
- I know that. I just...

95
00:10:26.668 --> 00:10:31.673
Anything. Did something slip?
Anybody... hanging out. anything slide?

96
00:10:31.756 --> 00:10:34.466
- Anything?
- No. nothing. Not a peep.

97
00:10:37.762 --> 00:10:38.971
What does he want?

98
00:10:39.931 --> 00:10:41.891
Guy says he's got answers that I need.

99
00:10:43.768 --> 00:10:44.769
Schoonover...

100
00:10:45.269 --> 00:10:47.897
you know. when I put him down.
he said something to me.

101
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:50.983
He said that what...

102
00:10:51.608 --> 00:10:54.195
He said that what happened
to Maria and the kids.

103
00:10:54.278 --> 00:10:56.489
it was because of something that I did.

104
00:10:56.781 --> 00:11:00.076
Something... something I did in Kandahar.

105
00:11:00.159 --> 00:11:01.243
Schoonover...

106
00:11:01.744 --> 00:11:03.744
Dirty bastard would've said anything
to stay alive.

107
00:11:04.121 --> 00:11:05.331
Doesn't mean it's not true.

108
00:11:06.248 --> 00:11:08.334
Come on. talk to me. What were you into?

109
00:11:11.754 --> 00:11:12.755
[muttering]

110
00:11:15.132 --> 00:11:16.342
Yeah...

111
00:11:17.009 --> 00:11:18.344
[muttering]

112
00:11:20.596 --> 00:11:24.308
There was a group of us.
We got sheep dipped to CIA.

113
00:11:24.392 --> 00:11:25.267
It was...

114
00:11:25.351 --> 00:11:28.395
interrogation and assassination. It was...

115
00:11:28.479 --> 00:11:29.688
It wasn't war.

116
00:11:30.606 --> 00:11:31.733
Not like we knew it.

117
00:11:33.025 --> 00:11:35.945
Truth is. Curt... I was past caring.

118
00:11:37.238 --> 00:11:39.365
That shit follows you home
no matter how hard you try.

119
00:11:39.448 --> 00:11:41.700
it follows you home.
and Maria. she knew it.

120
00:11:41.784 --> 00:11:43.577
She knew it. The kids knew it. the...

121
00:11:44.578 --> 00:11:46.455
Sometimes I'd catch 'em. they...

122
00:11:46.873 --> 00:11:49.291
They'd be looking at me
and they'd have this look.

123
00:11:50.334 --> 00:11:52.753
Look at me like
they didn't even know who I was.

124
00:11:53.587 --> 00:11:54.839
Come on. Frank.

125
00:11:54.922 --> 00:11:56.924
Come on. you...
you didn't kill your family.

126
00:11:57.008 --> 00:11:58.175
What if I did?

127
00:12:08.394 --> 00:12:10.479
It keeps hitting me. being back here.

128
00:12:11.814 --> 00:12:14.608
All the big stuff we take for granted
and don't even think about.

129
00:12:14.691 --> 00:12:16.944
but we obsess on things that don't matter.

130
00:12:17.027 --> 00:12:21.282
Think about what happened here on 9/11.
People bounce back so damn quick.

131
00:12:21.740 --> 00:12:24.952
- We let ourselves forget.
- We choose to forget.

132
00:12:25.036 --> 00:12:27.496
Easiest thing for me now
would be to forget Ahmad Zubair

133
00:12:27.579 --> 00:12:28.956
and what happened in Afghanistan.

134
00:12:32.418 --> 00:12:34.586
Why do you think Zubair was killed
by our people?

135
00:12:35.712 --> 00:12:38.424
I was sent a video file of his murder
by an anonymous source.

136
00:12:38.507 --> 00:12:41.468
He was interrogated
and shot in the head by Americans

137
00:12:41.552 --> 00:12:43.137
'cause they knew he was a cop.

138
00:12:43.721 --> 00:12:44.721
Holy shit.

139
00:12:45.139 --> 00:12:48.851
- Why haven't you shown Wolf the video?
- Because I don't have it.

140
00:12:49.768 --> 00:12:50.978
It was stolen in Kandahar.

141
00:12:51.062 --> 00:12:53.022
So. Schoonover and Castle
were on this tape?

142
00:12:53.606 --> 00:12:54.815
They all wore masks.

143
00:12:55.942 --> 00:12:59.403
All right. look. say it was them.
All your suspects are dead.

144
00:12:59.486 --> 00:13:01.572
Then who stole the tape?
And why am I back here?

145
00:13:01.655 --> 00:13:03.991
There were seven men
in the room with Zubair.

146
00:13:04.075 --> 00:13:05.409
Wolf knows about this?

147
00:13:05.492 --> 00:13:07.453
Well. why request me
and then treat me like shit?

148
00:13:07.536 --> 00:13:10.331
I think he's been told specifically
to keep me away from it.

149
00:13:12.249 --> 00:13:15.377
I found a guy from Castle
and Schoonover's old unit in the city.

150
00:13:16.087 --> 00:13:18.172
Guy called Billy Russo.

151
00:13:19.590 --> 00:13:21.425
Wolf's never gonna let you talk to him.

152
00:13:21.884 --> 00:13:23.302
We'll see about that.

153
00:13:31.518 --> 00:13:34.355
[Wolf] Okay. that's it.
I look forward to reading the report.

154
00:13:38.400 --> 00:13:39.443
Sir?

155
00:13:40.652 --> 00:13:41.863
Madani. How can I help you?

156
00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:43.786
Sir. I was going through
the deployment reports

157
00:13:43.822 --> 00:13:46.117
and special response protocols.
You got a great team here.

158
00:13:46.200 --> 00:13:48.702
You were in the field plenty yourself
as I understand it.

159
00:13:48.785 --> 00:13:51.163
I was always happy being the first one
through the door.

160
00:13:51.247 --> 00:13:53.607
The problem with rank is
they don't let you do that anymore.

161
00:13:53.833 --> 00:13:54.875
Of course.

162
00:13:54.959 --> 00:13:57.879
It'd be great for me to get
some physical training with the unit.

163
00:13:57.962 --> 00:14:00.214
You expect me to sign off
on sending my team to Brunswick

164
00:14:00.297 --> 00:14:02.884
on a getting-to-know-you exercise
purely for your benefit?

165
00:14:03.675 --> 00:14:04.718
Absolutely not.

166
00:14:04.801 --> 00:14:07.179
I thought we could organize
something up here in New York.

167
00:14:07.263 --> 00:14:09.056
via a private contractor.

168
00:14:09.140 --> 00:14:12.101
There's a company. Anvil.
that have all the facilities we'd need.

169
00:14:12.768 --> 00:14:14.686
I want you to be confident
that you can trust me

170
00:14:14.770 --> 00:14:16.130
if I'm the first through the door.

171
00:14:17.273 --> 00:14:18.399
What the hell. why not?

172
00:14:18.482 --> 00:14:20.776
Send me a proposal later
and I'll take a look at it.

173
00:14:20.985 --> 00:14:21.985
Thank you. sir.

174
00:14:29.827 --> 00:14:33.831
[Frank] Say. lady. I'm real hungry.
You got any change? Please?

175
00:14:37.626 --> 00:14:38.835
Thanks. Karen.

176
00:14:45.342 --> 00:14:46.635
You're still all heart. huh?

177
00:14:51.682 --> 00:14:53.059
Things got this bad. Frank?

178
00:14:54.018 --> 00:14:57.313
Wanted to say hello.
I thought I'd try my luck out here

179
00:14:57.396 --> 00:14:59.273
- and not get my head blown off.
- [scoffs]

180
00:15:00.607 --> 00:15:03.652
- You still got that hand cannon?
- You better believe it.

181
00:15:05.112 --> 00:15:07.823
- Attagirl.
- What the hell are you doing here?

182
00:15:09.325 --> 00:15:10.910
Can we talk?

183
00:15:13.620 --> 00:15:15.081
[door unlocks]

184
00:15:18.542 --> 00:15:19.626
[door closes]

185
00:15:25.841 --> 00:15:27.176
[Karen sighs]

186
00:15:30.096 --> 00:15:31.097
Drink?

187
00:15:34.475 --> 00:15:35.601
Sure.

188
00:15:42.233 --> 00:15:45.361
- I wasn't sure if you'd still talk to me.
- I wasn't either.

189
00:15:52.368 --> 00:15:53.660
You look well.

190
00:15:55.746 --> 00:15:58.874
Rocking the whole. uh... hipster thing.

191
00:15:59.458 --> 00:16:01.877
Been flirting with the idea
of going full man-bun.

192
00:16:01.961 --> 00:16:04.171
You. uh. think I could pull that off?

193
00:16:07.299 --> 00:16:08.342
Where have you been?

194
00:16:11.303 --> 00:16:12.846
[sighs] I had business. Karen.

195
00:16:14.181 --> 00:16:15.557
I had to finish.

196
00:16:16.642 --> 00:16:17.977
And you finished it?

197
00:16:32.699 --> 00:16:34.410
Look. Karen. there's. uh...

198
00:16:35.452 --> 00:16:37.204
there's somebody that knows
I'm still alive.

199
00:16:38.580 --> 00:16:41.542
- I need to know if you said anything.
- God. no.

200
00:16:42.584 --> 00:16:45.462
No. Frank. you should know me
better than that. I would never...

201
00:16:45.546 --> 00:16:47.840
You want to say no. you say no. but...

202
00:16:49.675 --> 00:16:51.343
I could really use your help.

203
00:16:54.846 --> 00:16:56.515
You want me to help you find them?

204
00:16:58.809 --> 00:16:59.893
I do.

205
00:17:00.686 --> 00:17:04.273
Look. this guy calls himself Micro. right?
Like that's supposed to mean something.

206
00:17:04.773 --> 00:17:07.068
He's been watching me.
I think he's some kind of spook

207
00:17:07.151 --> 00:17:09.778
and he's gotta be a good one.
'cause I didn't see him coming.

208
00:17:10.487 --> 00:17:12.364
And all you got's a name?

209
00:17:12.448 --> 00:17:15.117
He said something about
us both being dead men. right?

210
00:17:15.201 --> 00:17:18.745
About... me not being
the only ghost in New York.

211
00:17:20.747 --> 00:17:22.083
How do I contact you?

212
00:17:32.634 --> 00:17:35.554
- You bought me flowers?
- Yeah.

213
00:17:37.348 --> 00:17:39.308
I'm an old-fashioned kinda guy.

214
00:17:39.391 --> 00:17:42.478
I was thinking if you had something.
you could put the flowers in the window.

215
00:17:43.229 --> 00:17:44.480
I'll call you.

216
00:17:46.648 --> 00:17:47.648
Okay.

217
00:17:48.609 --> 00:17:50.736
- Okay.
- Okay.

218
00:17:53.655 --> 00:17:55.074
Thanks. Karen.

219
00:17:59.828 --> 00:18:01.872
Thanks for the beer. You know. hey...

220
00:18:15.177 --> 00:18:18.388
- Just really good to see you.
- Mmm. It's good to see you.

221
00:18:23.310 --> 00:18:24.394
[Frank] Be careful.

222
00:18:28.649 --> 00:18:30.109
[door opens]

223
00:18:33.904 --> 00:18:37.073
Okay. Uh. yeah. these can
go back downstairs. but wait...

224
00:18:38.408 --> 00:18:39.701
Uh... okay.

225
00:18:40.161 --> 00:18:41.995
All that can go downstairs now. thanks.

226
00:18:42.954 --> 00:18:43.955
[Ellison] Hey.

227
00:18:44.039 --> 00:18:46.208
- Good. you're here.
- Dare I ask?

228
00:18:46.292 --> 00:18:49.044
Well. our system has an entry
for an unpublished article

229
00:18:49.128 --> 00:18:52.298
from a year or so ago. but I can't find
the actual report on the system.

230
00:18:52.381 --> 00:18:55.342
The only other mention I could find
is a website. but that's not working.

231
00:18:55.426 --> 00:18:57.928
- And what was the article about?
- Computer hacker.

232
00:18:58.011 --> 00:19:01.014
Hey. would the name Micro
ring any bells for you?

233
00:19:01.097 --> 00:19:03.642
A government agent maybe.
but I'm not really sure.

234
00:19:04.351 --> 00:19:07.563
Where is this. um...
Where's this story coming from?

235
00:19:07.646 --> 00:19:09.686
A source I trust.
He gave me a name. told me to dig.

236
00:19:09.731 --> 00:19:12.067
- And. uh. who... who is this source?
- It's a source.

237
00:19:13.277 --> 00:19:16.488
- Tell you if it turns into anything.
- Ah. well. um...

238
00:19:17.281 --> 00:19:18.574
there... there was a story.

239
00:19:18.657 --> 00:19:21.993
brought in a while back by a stringer.
a real seat-of-your-pants radical.

240
00:19:22.077 --> 00:19:25.080
[stammers] Just paranoid.
Saw conspiracies in everything.

241
00:19:25.164 --> 00:19:28.124
But supposedly
he had a lead on an NSA analyst

242
00:19:28.209 --> 00:19:30.586
who was leaking secrets
who went by the name of Micro.

243
00:19:30.669 --> 00:19:31.712
And?

244
00:19:33.672 --> 00:19:35.424
And I decided not to run it.

245
00:19:35.507 --> 00:19:37.843
- Because?
- 'Cause I'm an editor. It's what I do.

246
00:19:37.926 --> 00:19:39.196
- Part of the job description.
- No.

247
00:19:39.220 --> 00:19:41.597
No. Ellison. don't get sarcastic with me.
I know that play.

248
00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:44.308
- Why?
- Well. he had no evidence. Karen.

249
00:19:44.808 --> 00:19:47.519
[stutters] I mean. his only source
was this guy from Homeland

250
00:19:47.603 --> 00:19:49.521
who refused to go on record.

251
00:19:49.605 --> 00:19:54.067
[sighs] And then... special agent
in charge for New York. Carson Wolf.

252
00:19:54.150 --> 00:19:57.404
stopped by personally
and asked me not to pursue it.

253
00:19:57.488 --> 00:19:58.822
So then the story is true?

254
00:19:58.905 --> 00:20:03.076
According to him. if we ran the story.
it would interfere with his investigation.

255
00:20:03.159 --> 00:20:05.871
He was afraid we'd screw up his chances
of catching everybody.

256
00:20:05.954 --> 00:20:08.999
- And you agreed with that?
- I decided to wait for the bigger story.

257
00:20:09.082 --> 00:20:12.836
- And make a friend of Carson Wolf.
- Oh. my God. Ellison...

258
00:20:14.213 --> 00:20:15.255
All right. look...

259
00:20:15.922 --> 00:20:20.261
I'm sure that I still have that article
in my office...

260
00:20:21.136 --> 00:20:24.765
so if I give it to you.
will you stop looking at me like that?

261
00:20:25.849 --> 00:20:26.849
[exhales]

262
00:20:45.952 --> 00:20:47.538
[beeping]

263
00:20:49.581 --> 00:20:51.207
[typing]

264
00:20:51.292 --> 00:20:55.170
[Sarah] But I don't care if Jason's mom
said he could go. You're not going. Zach.

265
00:20:55.837 --> 00:20:59.174
- [Zach] I already said I could go.
- [Sarah scoffs] Yeah. before you asked me.

266
00:20:59.258 --> 00:21:00.978
[Zach] Because I thought it would be okay.

267
00:21:01.009 --> 00:21:02.469
[Leo] That was your first mistake.

268
00:21:02.553 --> 00:21:03.988
[Zach] No one asked for your opinion.

269
00:21:04.012 --> 00:21:06.052
[Sarah] No one obviously asked me
for mine. either.

270
00:21:06.097 --> 00:21:08.642
[Zach] It's just a movie.
Dad would have totally let me go.

271
00:21:08.725 --> 00:21:10.185
[Sarah] When? When you were ten?

272
00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:12.271
Because your father
hasn't been here for a year.

273
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:16.358
which sucks for all of us.
but his memory isn't some bargaining chip

274
00:21:16.442 --> 00:21:19.027
that you can just throw out there
in an argument. You understand?

275
00:21:19.110 --> 00:21:20.404
I'm sorry. Mom.

276
00:21:21.363 --> 00:21:23.483
- He didn't mean it like that.
- [stutters] Hey. Zach!

277
00:21:24.074 --> 00:21:26.743
Zach. get back here. Come here.

278
00:21:26.827 --> 00:21:29.746
I get it. Maybe it is just a movie.
Maybe it is no big deal.

279
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:33.459
But I need to know what's going on
with all of us. or I can't... [stutters]

280
00:21:35.377 --> 00:21:36.628
I just need to know. okay?

281
00:21:38.380 --> 00:21:40.256
Control freakery is a coping mechanism.

282
00:21:40.341 --> 00:21:41.633
- [Sarah chuckles]
- I get that.

283
00:21:41.717 --> 00:21:42.884
[Sarah] Yeah. maybe it is.

284
00:21:42.968 --> 00:21:44.970
You know who I learned it from?
Your father.

285
00:21:46.305 --> 00:21:48.181
[Leo] It is just a movie. Mom.

286
00:21:49.140 --> 00:21:50.980
- [Zach] Please?
- [Sarah] I'll think about it.

287
00:21:51.017 --> 00:21:53.562
- When are you gonna think about it...
- Just... Hey!

288
00:21:53.645 --> 00:21:55.814
Quit while you're ahead. little brother.

289
00:21:57.941 --> 00:21:59.443
I love you. Mom.

290
00:21:59.901 --> 00:22:02.278
Oh. baby. I love you.

291
00:22:04.197 --> 00:22:06.325
[sighs] Me too. little bunny.

292
00:22:22.591 --> 00:22:24.676
- Are you finished with your math test?
- Yeah.

293
00:23:01.046 --> 00:23:02.673
- [device explodes]
- [man groaning]

294
00:23:04.174 --> 00:23:06.593
- [guns firing]
- [men grunting]

295
00:23:14.643 --> 00:23:15.936
[screams]

296
00:23:16.019 --> 00:23:19.022
- [man] Please. don't shoot! Don't shoot!
- [Dinah] It's a hostage.

297
00:23:19.105 --> 00:23:20.356
[grunts]

298
00:23:21.442 --> 00:23:23.902
- [alarm sounding]
- [Sam] God damn it.

299
00:23:26.780 --> 00:23:28.782
[sighs] I saw the guy
coming at me and I just...

300
00:23:28.865 --> 00:23:31.577
I figured he was a hostile. [sighs]

301
00:23:31.660 --> 00:23:32.744
[Dinah] Shh.

302
00:23:33.787 --> 00:23:35.914
- [Sam sighs]
- Don't beat yourself up.

303
00:23:35.997 --> 00:23:38.597
If we got out of a situation like this
with only one hostage dead.

304
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:41.503
- it'd be a win. It's never this clean.
- [man] Very true.

305
00:23:42.212 --> 00:23:44.255
The real thing is always messier.

306
00:23:44.339 --> 00:23:48.051
- I'm Billy Russo.
- Dinah Madani. Sam Stein.

307
00:23:48.134 --> 00:23:50.261
- This your operation?
- Yes. it is.

308
00:23:50.345 --> 00:23:54.099
We rent a different space every time
and they're a little rough and ready.

309
00:23:54.182 --> 00:23:56.582
- but it keeps people on their toes.
- Well. it worked great.

310
00:23:57.102 --> 00:23:58.979
Sam. you did everything right.

311
00:23:59.062 --> 00:24:02.148
You can't legislate for that
one terrified hostage who doesn't listen.

312
00:24:02.232 --> 00:24:05.902
Once somebody says go.
it's all just a percentages game.

313
00:24:05.986 --> 00:24:07.446
I'll keep that in mind.

314
00:24:09.573 --> 00:24:10.657
Please.

315
00:24:11.950 --> 00:24:14.911
Anvil would be happy
to give your people more training.

316
00:24:15.411 --> 00:24:17.539
- Thanks.
- There's none better.

317
00:24:17.623 --> 00:24:21.084
All my operators and instructors
are former Special Forces.

318
00:24:21.167 --> 00:24:25.255
A government contract here.
on US soil. would be a big deal for us.

319
00:24:25.839 --> 00:24:27.340
Where are your guys now?

320
00:24:27.423 --> 00:24:29.593
- Iraq and Afghanistan. mostly.
- Ah.

321
00:24:29.676 --> 00:24:32.554
Close protection work.
Convoy security. that kind of thing.

322
00:24:32.638 --> 00:24:33.680
We do good work.

323
00:24:33.764 --> 00:24:36.600
- We're growing fast.
- I just got back from Afghanistan.

324
00:24:36.683 --> 00:24:39.102
I was the Homeland Security attaché
over there.

325
00:24:39.185 --> 00:24:41.730
Madani. So. you're what. Persian?

326
00:24:41.813 --> 00:24:46.943
American. I was born here.
But. yeah. my folks came over in '79.

327
00:24:47.027 --> 00:24:49.946
Can't have been easy...
doing your job out there.

328
00:24:50.030 --> 00:24:53.575
The rules are simpler in many ways.
You know what they are. at least.

329
00:24:53.658 --> 00:24:54.658
Sure.

330
00:24:54.993 --> 00:24:56.828
Afghanistan's the simplest place
in the world.

331
00:24:56.912 --> 00:24:58.539
once you stop trying to change it.

332
00:24:59.497 --> 00:25:01.291
My last tour before I went private.

333
00:25:01.750 --> 00:25:03.919
Ah. Uh. what unit?

334
00:25:04.002 --> 00:25:05.962
Interrogating the help. Madani?

335
00:25:06.922 --> 00:25:08.256
Sir. I didn't know you were here.

336
00:25:08.339 --> 00:25:11.092
Mr. Russo. Carson Wolf.

337
00:25:11.176 --> 00:25:13.970
- Impressive setup you have here.
- I'm glad you approve.

338
00:25:14.470 --> 00:25:16.190
If you want to come by
the corporate office.

339
00:25:16.222 --> 00:25:17.992
I'd be happy to discuss
tailoring a program...

340
00:25:18.016 --> 00:25:19.350
Talk to procurement.

341
00:25:20.518 --> 00:25:23.188
Kandahar's in your rearview.
Don't forget that.

342
00:25:23.271 --> 00:25:25.566
Yes. sir. Just making conversation.

343
00:25:33.865 --> 00:25:37.243
I assume you can talk
about whatever you like off-duty?

344
00:25:38.745 --> 00:25:39.830
Over a drink?

345
00:26:11.278 --> 00:26:13.154
I wanna know what you're gonna do...

346
00:26:14.030 --> 00:26:15.281
if you find Micro.

347
00:26:16.616 --> 00:26:17.617
You found him?

348
00:26:20.078 --> 00:26:23.039
I found something.
Makes sense with what you told me.

349
00:26:24.457 --> 00:26:27.377
- Who is it?
- Look. I gotta be real clear here.

350
00:26:28.336 --> 00:26:30.496
I wanna help.
but not if it's gonna get someone killed.

351
00:26:30.546 --> 00:26:33.884
Hey. look. I didn't go looking
for this guy. all right? He came to me.

352
00:26:33.967 --> 00:26:35.844
For all I know.
this guy has something to do

353
00:26:35.927 --> 00:26:38.513
with what happened to my family.
So what do you want?

354
00:26:38.596 --> 00:26:40.436
If this guy isn't dirty.
if he's not dangerous.

355
00:26:40.515 --> 00:26:42.225
he's got nothing to worry about from me.

356
00:26:42.851 --> 00:26:44.019
Please. just...

357
00:26:44.853 --> 00:26:46.980
- just help me. Karen. Help me.
- [sighs]

358
00:26:47.063 --> 00:26:49.440
You know what? Or don't. all right?
Leave my ass in the wind

359
00:26:49.524 --> 00:26:52.402
if that's what you gotta do.
Just do it. all right? For Christ's sake.

360
00:26:52.736 --> 00:26:53.945
[sighs]

361
00:27:01.036 --> 00:27:02.162
What is this?

362
00:27:03.538 --> 00:27:05.373
It's an unconfirmed story... [sighs]

363
00:27:05.456 --> 00:27:08.669
...about an intelligence operative that
got caught leaking covert information.

364
00:27:10.211 --> 00:27:12.172
- Called himself Micro.
- Micro?

365
00:27:13.089 --> 00:27:14.507
You got a name?

366
00:27:14.841 --> 00:27:16.259
David Lieberman.

367
00:27:16.968 --> 00:27:19.262
And here's the kicker. Officially...

368
00:27:19.345 --> 00:27:23.224
Lieberman was shot and killed trying
to escape arrest by Homeland Security.

369
00:27:23.308 --> 00:27:25.268
I know. he said that.
He said that he was a ghost.

370
00:27:25.351 --> 00:27:26.352
- He said that.
- Yeah.

371
00:27:26.936 --> 00:27:28.396
How come I couldn't find this?

372
00:27:28.479 --> 00:27:30.273
- Well. the story never ran.
- Why?

373
00:27:30.356 --> 00:27:33.318
Because that guy.
Carson Wolf. got it shut down.

374
00:27:33.401 --> 00:27:35.278
You know what?
It's all in the story. Frank.

375
00:27:35.361 --> 00:27:36.947
Just read it.

376
00:27:37.906 --> 00:27:40.075
Hey. can I be honest with you?
This guy. he's...

377
00:27:41.076 --> 00:27:44.245
- he's scaring the shit out of me.
- What's he got on you anyway. huh?

378
00:27:46.581 --> 00:27:47.582
Nothing.

379
00:27:48.959 --> 00:27:50.001
Right.

380
00:27:51.586 --> 00:27:53.421
- Thanks for this.
- Yeah.

381
00:27:56.717 --> 00:27:58.009
Hey. when am I gonna see you?

382
00:28:00.679 --> 00:28:01.721
You want to?

383
00:28:03.932 --> 00:28:06.351
It'd mean you're still alive. [scoffs]

384
00:28:07.435 --> 00:28:10.063
Believe it or not.
I actually care what happens to you...

385
00:28:10.146 --> 00:28:12.023
which makes precisely one of us.

386
00:28:16.778 --> 00:28:17.821
Just. uh...

387
00:28:21.241 --> 00:28:22.241
be careful.

388
00:28:37.215 --> 00:28:39.217
[pop song playing over speakers]

389
00:28:43.221 --> 00:28:44.264
[tires screech]

390
00:28:44.347 --> 00:28:46.432
- [Sarah gasps] Oh. my God.
- [Frank grunts]

391
00:28:47.017 --> 00:28:48.810
- Oh. my God. I am so sorry.
- [groans]

392
00:28:48.894 --> 00:28:50.854
[stutters] I didn't even see you.

393
00:28:56.777 --> 00:28:58.945
- Stay down. Stay down. um...
- [groaning] Okay. Yeah.

394
00:28:59.029 --> 00:29:01.423
- I'm gonna call the paramedics.
- No. no. no. It's all right.

395
00:29:01.447 --> 00:29:03.867
Sir. I really think you should stay down.
Just wait for help.

396
00:29:03.950 --> 00:29:05.510
Yeah. no. look. there's nothing broken.

397
00:29:05.535 --> 00:29:08.055
- I think we both got lucky. you know.
- Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

398
00:29:11.332 --> 00:29:14.294
Kinda came out of there.
I didn't give you much of a chance. so...

399
00:29:14.377 --> 00:29:15.378
Your head is bleeding.

400
00:29:16.337 --> 00:29:18.214
No. no. no. no. no.

401
00:29:22.052 --> 00:29:24.012
No. Where are you going. Sarah?

402
00:29:29.642 --> 00:29:30.685
No!

403
00:29:30.769 --> 00:29:32.896
No. no. no. Castle. you asshole.

404
00:29:34.689 --> 00:29:37.608
Shit. [sighs]

405
00:29:46.409 --> 00:29:47.828
[engine starts]

406
00:29:52.248 --> 00:29:53.541
[grunts softly]

407
00:29:53.624 --> 00:29:55.001
[cell phone vibrating]

408
00:29:58.463 --> 00:29:59.463
[scoffs]

409
00:30:08.098 --> 00:30:09.891
Thanks for that. As good as new.

410
00:30:09.975 --> 00:30:13.478
- Um. I was making myself a pot. So...
- Wow. Uh. you didn't have to do that.

411
00:30:13.561 --> 00:30:15.355
- Oh. please... [chuckles]
- Thank you.

412
00:30:15.438 --> 00:30:19.109
It's the least I could do after
spilling yours all over my windshield.

413
00:30:19.192 --> 00:30:20.902
I'm fine. I tell you. It's...

414
00:30:21.862 --> 00:30:25.406
- It's good. I'm. uh...
- [sighs] It's a mess.

415
00:30:25.490 --> 00:30:27.575
I'm Pete. by the way. Castiglione.

416
00:30:27.658 --> 00:30:29.911
- Uh. Sarah. Lieberman.
- Pleasure.

417
00:30:31.788 --> 00:30:33.832
You got a good-looking family. Sarah.

418
00:30:34.833 --> 00:30:35.667
Thank you.

419
00:30:35.750 --> 00:30:37.710
What line of work's your husband in?

420
00:30:38.503 --> 00:30:40.005
Uh. he works for the government.

421
00:30:40.588 --> 00:30:43.049
He. um... he actually passed away.

422
00:30:44.092 --> 00:30:45.510
A year ago.

423
00:30:46.887 --> 00:30:47.989
- [sighs]
- Sorry to hear that.

424
00:30:48.013 --> 00:30:51.432
[stammers] Yeah. I'm sorry.
I don't know why I was gonna lie.

425
00:30:52.683 --> 00:30:54.269
[Sarah sighs]

426
00:30:54.352 --> 00:30:56.146
You know. I get it. Uh...

427
00:30:57.230 --> 00:31:00.483
Must be difficult. You got a strange man
in the house and he's not...

428
00:31:01.567 --> 00:31:03.694
I'll take off. all right?
I'll just set this coffee...

429
00:31:03.778 --> 00:31:05.738
No. no. no. no. no.
It's okay. Please. sorry.

430
00:31:05.821 --> 00:31:07.615
Um... finish your coffee.

431
00:31:08.616 --> 00:31:09.616
Okay.

432
00:31:19.210 --> 00:31:21.546
I'm sorry about your loss. Sarah.

433
00:31:23.965 --> 00:31:24.966
[sniffles]

434
00:31:27.760 --> 00:31:29.721
Oh. Uh...

435
00:31:30.055 --> 00:31:34.475
I'm sorry. it's just the...
the whole knocking you down and...

436
00:31:35.601 --> 00:31:38.438
I mean. you think...
you think you're okay and then...

437
00:31:38.521 --> 00:31:40.356
[sighs]
...something just brings it all back.

438
00:31:40.773 --> 00:31:41.773
Yeah.

439
00:31:42.067 --> 00:31:46.029
Uh. I didn't mean to ambush you
with the whole dead husband thing.

440
00:31:46.112 --> 00:31:49.532
It's just. you know. new people. do I lie?

441
00:31:50.491 --> 00:31:53.494
But then that feels so disloyal
to his memories.

442
00:31:54.787 --> 00:31:57.958
You must think I'm crazy.
Knocking you down and then...

443
00:31:58.041 --> 00:32:00.626
No. no. Hey. hey.
I don't. uh... Not at all.

444
00:32:00.710 --> 00:32:03.004
- Sarah. you know. I. uh...
- [sighs]

445
00:32:03.922 --> 00:32:06.257
I lost my family. All of 'em.

446
00:32:07.133 --> 00:32:08.718
It wasn't... It wasn't too long ago.

447
00:32:08.801 --> 00:32:11.637
Not a day goes by. right?
You wish things were different.

448
00:32:11.721 --> 00:32:14.015
[stutters] You wish that you had
done something different.

449
00:32:14.098 --> 00:32:15.475
And... and you feel guilty.

450
00:32:16.476 --> 00:32:19.229
You know. that you're still here
and they're not.

451
00:32:20.563 --> 00:32:23.649
Your husband. was he. uh... Was he ill?

452
00:32:24.275 --> 00:32:26.652
[clears throat] Uh. no. Um. David...

453
00:32:27.903 --> 00:32:31.157
David died doing something very brave...

454
00:32:32.575 --> 00:32:33.784
and really stupid.

455
00:32:35.286 --> 00:32:38.539
On my good days. you know.
I'm proud of him for what he did.

456
00:32:39.499 --> 00:32:43.794
And on my bad ones. I just wanna
scream in his face for being so selfish.

457
00:32:45.213 --> 00:32:47.423
Honestly. if he walked
through that door right now.

458
00:32:47.507 --> 00:32:49.550
I don't know if I would kiss him
or slap him.

459
00:32:52.803 --> 00:32:53.804
Yeah.

460
00:32:56.182 --> 00:32:57.433
[muttering]

461
00:33:01.437 --> 00:33:02.480
[line rings]

462
00:33:02.563 --> 00:33:04.149
[line beeps]

463
00:33:05.525 --> 00:33:06.668
- Come on. Frank.
- [line rings]

464
00:33:06.692 --> 00:33:07.943
[line beeps]

465
00:33:08.028 --> 00:33:09.154
[sighs]

466
00:33:11.447 --> 00:33:12.573
Come on.

467
00:33:12.657 --> 00:33:13.658
[grunts]

468
00:33:17.495 --> 00:33:19.664
[exhales sharply] Yeah.

469
00:33:26.504 --> 00:33:29.299
- [Sarah] Are you sure you're okay?
- [Frank] As good as new.

470
00:33:29.382 --> 00:33:32.177
Thank you for the. uh... For the coffee.
Take care of yourself.

471
00:33:32.260 --> 00:33:33.511
[Sarah] You. too.

472
00:33:35.263 --> 00:33:36.264
[sighs]

473
00:33:43.271 --> 00:33:46.607
- [grunts] God damn it!
- [honks]

474
00:33:47.650 --> 00:33:48.818
[garage door rattling]

475
00:33:53.614 --> 00:33:56.159
- Hey. I'm... I'm okay. [chuckles]
- Hey. Yeah?

476
00:33:56.242 --> 00:33:58.012
- Yeah. I'm really all right. Yeah.
- You sure?

477
00:33:58.036 --> 00:33:59.662
If you got any tools in there...

478
00:33:59.745 --> 00:34:02.582
- [stutters] ...I could take a look.
- [garage door continues rattling]

479
00:34:05.626 --> 00:34:07.545
[sniffles] Yeah.

480
00:34:07.628 --> 00:34:09.422
Yeah. that'd be nice.

481
00:34:24.312 --> 00:34:25.438
[typing]

482
00:35:06.437 --> 00:35:08.063
[Lisa laughing]

483
00:35:56.028 --> 00:35:57.697
[beeping]

484
00:36:06.581 --> 00:36:07.998
[sighs]

485
00:36:17.049 --> 00:36:18.259
[sighs]

486
00:36:19.677 --> 00:36:21.136
[alarm beeping]

487
00:36:30.188 --> 00:36:31.397
[beeping stops]

488
00:36:31.481 --> 00:36:32.690
[sighs]

489
00:36:40.740 --> 00:36:43.451
["Ain't That a Kick in the Head" playing]

490
00:36:47.663 --> 00:36:53.878
♪ How lucky can one guy be?
I kissed her and she kissed me ♪

491
00:36:54.837 --> 00:36:59.342
♪ Like the fella once said
Ain't that a kick in the head? ♪

492
00:37:02.136 --> 00:37:04.472
♪ The room was completely black ♪

493
00:37:05.806 --> 00:37:08.184
♪ I hugged her and she hugged back ♪

494
00:37:09.310 --> 00:37:13.898
♪ Like the sailor said. quote
"Ain't that a hole in the boat?" ♪

495
00:37:15.316 --> 00:37:20.947
♪ My head keeps spinning
I go to sleep and keep grinning ♪

496
00:37:22.031 --> 00:37:24.033
[both grunting]

497
00:37:27.287 --> 00:37:28.621
[Wolf yells]

498
00:37:30.623 --> 00:37:32.207
[both grunting]

499
00:37:34.460 --> 00:37:37.296
♪ It's just like the fella said ♪

500
00:37:38.089 --> 00:37:39.382
♪ Tell me quick ♪

501
00:37:39.465 --> 00:37:43.928
♪ Ain't love a kick in the head? ♪

502
00:37:59.568 --> 00:38:01.070
♪ Tell me quick ♪

503
00:38:02.530 --> 00:38:04.532
♪ Oh. ain't love a kick? ♪

504
00:38:06.575 --> 00:38:07.576
♪ Tell me quick ♪

505
00:38:08.035 --> 00:38:14.125
♪ Ain't love a kick in the head? ♪

506
00:38:21.799 --> 00:38:24.677
[Frank] Cut your shit.
I know you're awake.

507
00:38:31.684 --> 00:38:32.977
Who are you?

508
00:38:34.354 --> 00:38:37.440
Whoever you are. this is
the stupidest thing you've ever done.

509
00:38:38.483 --> 00:38:41.193
And it's getting stupider every second.

510
00:38:41.944 --> 00:38:43.988
You do know who I am. don't you?

511
00:38:44.739 --> 00:38:47.533
You're the guy who's gonna tell me
about David Lieberman.

512
00:38:47.617 --> 00:38:49.159
[inhales deeply] Who?

513
00:38:55.750 --> 00:38:57.960
- [grunts]
- [groans]

514
00:38:59.670 --> 00:39:00.921
Lieberman.

515
00:39:01.005 --> 00:39:03.591
The hacker. A man you put down.

516
00:39:03.674 --> 00:39:05.510
[chuckles]

517
00:39:07.637 --> 00:39:08.763
[grunts]

518
00:39:09.722 --> 00:39:11.056
[groans]

519
00:39:13.518 --> 00:39:16.020
[groaning]

520
00:39:17.522 --> 00:39:19.273
I know a little bit about this.

521
00:39:19.857 --> 00:39:23.778
I spent some time at Guantanamo.
in torture.

522
00:39:24.570 --> 00:39:27.490
It doesn't work. Not really.

523
00:39:27.573 --> 00:39:30.159
Any information given is suspect.

524
00:39:30.242 --> 00:39:32.286
If you were a professional.
you would know that.

525
00:39:33.413 --> 00:39:35.213
There's many ways
to get the truth out of a...

526
00:39:35.247 --> 00:39:38.459
Look. Lieberman was a traitor.
He was selling secrets.

527
00:39:38.543 --> 00:39:40.878
[panting] He was killed resisting...

528
00:39:40.961 --> 00:39:44.840
[screams] Ah. shit! God damn it!

529
00:39:44.924 --> 00:39:46.384
[yells]

530
00:39:48.177 --> 00:39:50.345
Way I see it.
there's no way a guy like you

531
00:39:50.430 --> 00:39:52.390
kills a suspect in a case that big.

532
00:39:52.473 --> 00:39:55.267
No way. Not unless you're dirty.

533
00:39:55.350 --> 00:39:57.687
So either someone paid you to do it...

534
00:39:57.770 --> 00:39:59.772
or you were working
with Schoonover already.

535
00:39:59.855 --> 00:40:01.816
I swear to God. I don't...

536
00:40:01.899 --> 00:40:04.819
[pants] ...I don't know anybody
named Schoonover.

537
00:40:04.902 --> 00:40:07.613
Nothing about heroin from Kandahar either.
is that the case?

538
00:40:07.697 --> 00:40:09.907
You just answered your own question.

539
00:40:09.990 --> 00:40:12.410
- Is that right? [shushing]
- [panting]

540
00:40:13.368 --> 00:40:16.622
[screaming] Shit!

541
00:40:16.706 --> 00:40:19.041
So no matter whoever's
makin' you afraid to talk.

542
00:40:19.124 --> 00:40:21.794
- I promise you. whatever you think...
- [yells]

543
00:40:21.877 --> 00:40:23.921
- [grunts]
- [breathing heavily] Freeze.

544
00:40:24.004 --> 00:40:26.173
Don't even think about it.
Get on your knees.

545
00:40:26.549 --> 00:40:27.550
Do it!

546
00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:32.597
And put your hands behind your head. now.

547
00:40:32.680 --> 00:40:34.181
[breathing heavily]

548
00:40:42.064 --> 00:40:43.190
Holy shit.

549
00:40:44.358 --> 00:40:46.235
You don't know how to die. do you?

550
00:40:46.736 --> 00:40:48.195
This is rich.

551
00:40:49.655 --> 00:40:51.240
[chuckles]

552
00:40:53.242 --> 00:40:54.952
You gonna read me my rights?

553
00:40:55.911 --> 00:40:56.954
No.

554
00:40:57.955 --> 00:40:59.790
I don't think I'm gonna do that.

555
00:41:00.833 --> 00:41:02.460
[panting]

556
00:41:03.418 --> 00:41:05.671
Tonight's the night
you're gonna die. Frank.

557
00:41:06.922 --> 00:41:08.883
The third time's the charm.

558
00:41:08.966 --> 00:41:11.176
The fricking Punisher?

559
00:41:12.136 --> 00:41:13.303
You're pathetic.

560
00:41:14.429 --> 00:41:17.016
I almost feel sorry for you.

561
00:41:17.099 --> 00:41:19.727
We knew exactly where you'd be.

562
00:41:19.810 --> 00:41:22.396
Exactly where to go to get you.

563
00:41:23.355 --> 00:41:28.068
You bored your squad shitless
talking about your homecoming tradition.

564
00:41:28.152 --> 00:41:30.237
Picnic in the park. Frank?

565
00:41:30.320 --> 00:41:33.699
You really were
your mama's little apple pie. weren't you?

566
00:41:33.783 --> 00:41:37.036
What're you saying?
You killed my family to get to me?

567
00:41:37.119 --> 00:41:38.287
Misdirection.

568
00:41:39.371 --> 00:41:41.624
A good player hides his hand. Frank.

569
00:41:41.707 --> 00:41:43.668
We figured if there were
enough dead bodies.

570
00:41:43.751 --> 00:41:47.588
nobody would really care to look
close enough at any given one of 'em.

571
00:41:47.672 --> 00:41:49.590
It was a calculated risk.

572
00:41:49.674 --> 00:41:51.258
You understand. right?

573
00:41:51.341 --> 00:41:54.136
And Lieberman. what about Lieberman?
Who's he?

574
00:41:54.219 --> 00:41:55.888
[panting]

575
00:41:58.724 --> 00:42:00.768
We thought you were the one
that sent him the tape.

576
00:42:01.811 --> 00:42:05.230
Now close your eyes. Frank.
I'm gonna do you a favor.

577
00:42:06.356 --> 00:42:08.693
You're gonna see your family real soon.

578
00:42:11.111 --> 00:42:12.111
No?

579
00:42:13.155 --> 00:42:14.198
Suit yourself.

580
00:42:14.823 --> 00:42:16.700
- [gun clicks]
- Gun's empty. asshole.

581
00:42:17.827 --> 00:42:19.494
- [grunting]
- [both yelling]

582
00:42:23.624 --> 00:42:24.834
[groans]

583
00:42:26.210 --> 00:42:27.461
[straining]

584
00:42:28.378 --> 00:42:30.590
It's just you. me and the truth now.

585
00:42:30.673 --> 00:42:32.091
- [grunts]
- [neck snaps]

586
00:42:36.470 --> 00:42:39.389
This is where you bring a girl
when you're trying to impress her?

587
00:42:39.473 --> 00:42:42.309
This is where I bring a girl
when she's gonna see through all that.

588
00:42:42.602 --> 00:42:45.229
[chuckles] I can't decide
whether that's a compliment or not.

589
00:42:45.896 --> 00:42:48.148
Are you the kind of woman
that takes offense at those?

590
00:42:48.232 --> 00:42:49.692
Depends who they're from.

591
00:42:50.359 --> 00:42:52.527
The last time I saw glasses this dirty.

592
00:42:52.612 --> 00:42:56.741
I was in the NCO's mess at Bagram.
saying my farewells to Afghanistan.

593
00:42:56.824 --> 00:42:58.158
Sounds like you miss it.

594
00:42:58.742 --> 00:43:02.162
- I had unfinished business.
- There's no end to anything there.

595
00:43:02.246 --> 00:43:05.249
Afghans have been fighting invaders
for a thousand years.

596
00:43:05.332 --> 00:43:08.460
For us. it's a mission.
For them. it's just... life.

597
00:43:09.044 --> 00:43:11.164
I finished my last tour
and I knew I couldn't go back.

598
00:43:11.213 --> 00:43:13.090
Not in uniform. anyway.

599
00:43:13.924 --> 00:43:15.718
You never said who you were with.

600
00:43:19.096 --> 00:43:21.807
Why do I get the feeling
that if I name the right unit.

601
00:43:21.891 --> 00:43:24.101
you're suddenly gonna get
a lot more interested?

602
00:43:25.728 --> 00:43:27.229
Marine Force Recon.

603
00:43:27.312 --> 00:43:30.024
Scout sniper specialist.
134 confirmed kills.

604
00:43:30.107 --> 00:43:32.860
Three tours of Iraq. One in Afghanistan.

605
00:43:32.943 --> 00:43:34.236
You read my file.

606
00:43:34.319 --> 00:43:36.321
I like to know
who's paying me compliments.

607
00:43:37.322 --> 00:43:40.117
Am I a suspect for something?

608
00:43:40.200 --> 00:43:41.595
Not according to your discharge records.

609
00:43:41.619 --> 00:43:43.913
Is that why you came to Anvil
for training?

610
00:43:43.996 --> 00:43:46.957
You figure I can help you
with this unfinished business of yours?

611
00:43:47.917 --> 00:43:49.126
I hope so. yeah.

612
00:43:50.294 --> 00:43:51.295
Excuse me.

613
00:43:54.339 --> 00:43:56.967
Well. I'm not about to throw shade
on my friends.

614
00:43:57.051 --> 00:43:59.261
In all due respect. Dinah. you're a cop.

615
00:44:00.721 --> 00:44:04.016
Soldiers can't question
legality or morality in the moment.

616
00:44:04.099 --> 00:44:05.539
That's a way to get yourself killed.

617
00:44:09.229 --> 00:44:11.982
[chuckles] Ask your questions.

618
00:44:14.819 --> 00:44:16.611
- You served with Frank Castle.
- [sighs]

619
00:44:16.696 --> 00:44:19.198
Yeah. Frank Castle was my best buddy.

620
00:44:20.700 --> 00:44:22.827
I guess that wasn't in my file. huh?

621
00:44:24.370 --> 00:44:26.580
A lot of those kills I got in one night...

622
00:44:27.331 --> 00:44:31.043
side by side with the guy. holed up
in a house in Basra with no backup.

623
00:44:31.960 --> 00:44:34.046
We spent the night trying not to die.

624
00:44:34.546 --> 00:44:36.924
One of the best nights of my life.
if I'm honest.

625
00:44:37.007 --> 00:44:39.426
It was just them or us. Who was better?

626
00:44:40.594 --> 00:44:42.054
There was nobody better than Frank.

627
00:44:46.141 --> 00:44:47.643
I'm sorry that he's dead.

628
00:44:49.103 --> 00:44:50.687
He took a lot of people with him.

629
00:44:50.771 --> 00:44:54.149
What? Drug dealers? Gangsters? Good.

630
00:44:54.233 --> 00:44:57.402
You shipped out. Castle didn't.
Did he get dirty?

631
00:44:57.486 --> 00:44:59.696
Stay in any war long enough.
it'll get dirty.

632
00:44:59.780 --> 00:45:02.366
Unless you've got something good
to hold onto.

633
00:45:02.449 --> 00:45:03.784
Frank had that taken away.

634
00:45:03.868 --> 00:45:05.511
Could he have been involved
in drugs there?

635
00:45:05.535 --> 00:45:06.703
[chuckles]

636
00:45:08.080 --> 00:45:11.500
If you knew the man.
you would know how dumb that question is.

637
00:45:11.583 --> 00:45:15.004
I think that the system let Frank down
in a big way.

638
00:45:15.587 --> 00:45:17.172
So he did what he was trained to do.

639
00:45:17.256 --> 00:45:19.674
So if someone killed your family.
you'd do the same?

640
00:45:19.759 --> 00:45:21.176
Well. I don't have one.

641
00:45:22.219 --> 00:45:24.054
I like to travel light. What about you?

642
00:45:26.556 --> 00:45:28.356
I think some of us
get to have the family life

643
00:45:28.433 --> 00:45:29.977
and some of us get to protect it.

644
00:45:30.895 --> 00:45:33.773
So... you're single.

645
00:45:35.775 --> 00:45:36.942
[chuckles]

646
00:45:39.403 --> 00:45:42.823
Uh... not worried
that'll get kind of lonely?

647
00:45:44.158 --> 00:45:45.367
I'm not lonely.

648
00:45:47.870 --> 00:45:48.870
Are you?

649
00:45:49.872 --> 00:45:51.081
Not right now.

650
00:45:52.958 --> 00:45:54.418
[cell phone chimes]

651
00:45:57.880 --> 00:45:59.214
I've gotta go.

652
00:45:59.298 --> 00:46:01.758
- Never off-duty. huh?
- Ah. sorry.

653
00:46:02.676 --> 00:46:05.637
Maybe we could do this again sometime?

654
00:46:07.472 --> 00:46:09.308
Yeah. I'd like that.

655
00:46:10.350 --> 00:46:13.103
Well. you know where to find me.

656
00:46:17.316 --> 00:46:19.734
Good night. Special Agent Madani.

657
00:46:21.862 --> 00:46:23.197
Happy hunting.

658
00:46:26.033 --> 00:46:28.327
- [camera shutter clicks]
- [indistinct radio chatter]

659
00:46:29.703 --> 00:46:31.496
- Good night?
- [Dinah] Show me.

660
00:46:31.580 --> 00:46:33.498
Well. this is gonna sober you up
real fast.

661
00:46:33.582 --> 00:46:35.334
I'm not drunk.

662
00:46:35.417 --> 00:46:37.086
Okay. I'm not judging.

663
00:46:37.169 --> 00:46:39.129
Holy shit.

664
00:46:39.213 --> 00:46:40.755
Holy shit indeed.

665
00:46:40.840 --> 00:46:42.925
[inhales deeply]
I never liked the guy. but still...

666
00:46:43.008 --> 00:46:46.220
this does not look like
a fun way to go... at all.

667
00:46:50.307 --> 00:46:52.726
They're waiting for permission
to move the body.

668
00:46:53.643 --> 00:46:55.520
You're the ranking agent now.

669
00:47:12.746 --> 00:47:14.248
Thank you. ma'am.

670
00:47:16.291 --> 00:47:17.877
[cell phone vibrates]

671
00:47:29.554 --> 00:47:33.600
So. let me guess. You're. uh...
you're outside. sunbathing on a roof.

672
00:47:34.059 --> 00:47:36.395
Oh. that's. uh... funny.

673
00:47:37.396 --> 00:47:38.772
Almost.

674
00:47:39.731 --> 00:47:41.251
- [beeping]
- Let me ask you something.

675
00:47:41.275 --> 00:47:45.279
How are the eggs over at
Pete's Diner and Grill in Sunnyside?

676
00:47:45.362 --> 00:47:46.363
Any good?

677
00:47:46.446 --> 00:47:49.033
- Smart work. spook.
- [stuttering] You know. uh. I...

678
00:47:49.116 --> 00:47:50.876
I gave you this phone
so I could contact you.

679
00:47:50.910 --> 00:47:51.994
You understand that. right?

680
00:47:52.077 --> 00:47:55.080
I know why you gave it to me.
but I wasn't gonna leave it on.

681
00:47:55.164 --> 00:47:58.542
See. thing is. is I. uh.
got a shave. hurt my leg.

682
00:47:58.625 --> 00:47:59.626
Got myself a limp.

683
00:47:59.709 --> 00:48:01.753
I guess it messed up
your gait recognition. huh?

684
00:48:01.836 --> 00:48:05.507
[chuckles] Yeah. I was wondering how long
it was gonna take you to catch on to that.

685
00:48:06.091 --> 00:48:09.636
Only thing I can't figure out
is how you knew which cameras to check.

686
00:48:09.719 --> 00:48:10.930
Oh. that was easy. Frank.

687
00:48:11.013 --> 00:48:13.015
I waited for a bunch of bad guys
to turn up dead

688
00:48:13.098 --> 00:48:14.766
and then I just checked nearby.

689
00:48:14.849 --> 00:48:16.143
Pretty smart. Lieberman.

690
00:48:16.226 --> 00:48:19.563
You know I did you a favor. right?
I wiped those feeds clean after.

691
00:48:19.646 --> 00:48:21.315
Boy. oh. boy. I'm. uh...

692
00:48:21.398 --> 00:48:23.067
- I'm real grateful.
- So. uh...

693
00:48:23.150 --> 00:48:27.404
here we are. couple of smart guys
chewing the fat. huh?

694
00:48:27.487 --> 00:48:29.239
I gotta ask you. why'd you go to my house?

695
00:48:31.700 --> 00:48:33.410
You know something. David?

696
00:48:33.953 --> 00:48:38.165
Your wife. she's. uh...
she's real cut up about your death.

697
00:48:38.248 --> 00:48:39.559
They have nothing to do with this.

698
00:48:39.583 --> 00:48:41.626
Bullshit. You know what?
You're an asshole.

699
00:48:42.211 --> 00:48:43.878
You're a man who put his family in danger

700
00:48:43.963 --> 00:48:45.683
and you didn't do it once.
you did it again.

701
00:48:45.755 --> 00:48:47.257
I'm gonna make that right.

702
00:48:48.342 --> 00:48:50.094
She's only safe if she thinks I'm dead.

703
00:48:50.177 --> 00:48:53.430
You brought this shit on yourself.
You wanted to play Deep Throat. right?

704
00:48:53.513 --> 00:48:54.681
Your buddy. Carson Wolf.

705
00:48:54.764 --> 00:48:57.309
- he told me everything.
- Did you kill him?

706
00:48:59.186 --> 00:49:00.354
It's what you wanted. right?

707
00:49:02.022 --> 00:49:03.232
What did he say?

708
00:49:03.315 --> 00:49:05.525
- You still want to talk?
- Yeah. I do.

709
00:49:05.609 --> 00:49:07.929
- Here's what we're gonna do...
- No. no. you stop talking.

710
00:49:07.987 --> 00:49:11.281
I'm sick of hearing you talk.
I'm calling the shots now.

711
00:49:11.365 --> 00:49:13.117
I'm going offline.

712
00:49:13.200 --> 00:49:14.201
In exactly one hour.

713
00:49:14.284 --> 00:49:16.662
call me with a cell phone number
I can reach you on.

714
00:49:16.745 --> 00:49:18.163
- You got that?
- [line disconnects]

715
00:49:26.005 --> 00:49:27.381
[Frank] Here's how it works.

716
00:49:27.464 --> 00:49:30.009
I give you a destination
and a time to be there.

717
00:49:30.092 --> 00:49:32.386
If you're late or if I spot tails.
we're done.

718
00:49:33.345 --> 00:49:36.306
Twenty minutes.
under the Pulaski Road Bridge.

719
00:49:41.645 --> 00:49:43.272
[cell phone vibrating]

720
00:49:45.524 --> 00:49:48.985
- Yeah.
- [Frank] 41st Street dock. 20 minutes.

721
00:49:49.069 --> 00:49:50.070
[line disconnects]

722
00:49:56.910 --> 00:49:58.328
[cell phone vibrating]

723
00:50:02.166 --> 00:50:04.418
[Frank]
Greenpoint Terminal. 20 minutes.

724
00:50:20.225 --> 00:50:21.435
[sighs]

725
00:50:22.644 --> 00:50:24.313
[cell phone vibrating]

726
00:50:30.485 --> 00:50:33.822
[Frank] Another 20 minutes.
Mount Zion Cemetery.

727
00:50:33.905 --> 00:50:35.949
- Hurry up. Lieberman.
- [line disconnects]

728
00:50:39.994 --> 00:50:41.246
Asshole.

729
00:50:48.795 --> 00:50:51.631
[Curtis] Hey. Frank.
Your boy's on his way.

730
00:50:51.715 --> 00:50:53.758
He's clean and alone.

731
00:50:53.842 --> 00:50:56.886
2002 blue Chevy Impala.

732
00:50:56.970 --> 00:51:00.099
Yeah. he's not expecting
any high-speed chases. that's for sure.

733
00:51:01.224 --> 00:51:02.224
Yeah.

734
00:51:08.815 --> 00:51:11.985
[Frank] I don't need to tell you
where to come. do I. David?

735
00:51:46.060 --> 00:51:48.062
- Whoa. whoa. whoa.
- Who are you?

736
00:51:48.980 --> 00:51:51.483
Castle has you in his crosshairs
right now. buddy.

737
00:51:52.401 --> 00:51:55.404
If you shoot me. you will be next.

738
00:51:55.487 --> 00:51:56.780
Why isn't he here?

739
00:51:56.863 --> 00:51:59.158
He decided he doesn't like
what you're selling.

740
00:51:59.866 --> 00:52:01.243
Frank's in the wind.

741
00:52:01.701 --> 00:52:04.871
If you try to find him again.
he will visit Sarah.

742
00:52:07.207 --> 00:52:09.042
He said you'd know what that meant.

743
00:52:10.293 --> 00:52:11.293
Hold on.

744
00:52:11.920 --> 00:52:13.087
Hey...

745
00:52:14.089 --> 00:52:15.089
Hey!

746
00:52:29.396 --> 00:52:30.980
Castle!

747
00:52:33.900 --> 00:52:35.235
You need me!

748
00:53:42.969 --> 00:53:44.388
[sighs]

749
00:53:46.055 --> 00:53:47.474
[muttering]

750
00:53:52.604 --> 00:53:55.565
No. no. no. Think. think. think. Come on.

751
00:53:55.649 --> 00:53:57.359
[inhales deeply]

752
00:53:57.442 --> 00:53:58.777
[sighs]

753
00:54:00.779 --> 00:54:01.780
Come on...

754
00:54:03.448 --> 00:54:04.658
[sighs]

755
00:54:06.826 --> 00:54:08.662
Think. think. think.

756
00:54:08.745 --> 00:54:10.204
What's going on?

757
00:54:11.205 --> 00:54:12.707
What are we doing? What are we doing?

758
00:54:14.208 --> 00:54:15.544
[sighs]

759
00:54:27.972 --> 00:54:29.182
[sighs]

760
00:54:43.572 --> 00:54:44.989
[laughs]

761
00:54:49.243 --> 00:54:50.329
Frank.

762
00:54:52.414 --> 00:54:53.498
- No.
- [grunts]

763
00:54:53.582 --> 00:54:54.791
[groans]

764
00:55:08.555 --> 00:55:10.474
[dramatic music playing]

764
